he variable definition `T t(std::declval<Args>()...);` is well-formed. Both `T` and all the types in `Args` must be complete types, `void`, or arrays of unknown bound.  \n  \n## Requirements  \n **Header:** <type_traits>  \n  \n **Namespace:** std  \n  \n## See Also  \n [<type_traits>](../standard-library/type-traits.md)\n\n\n\n"}